  "implemented_capabilities": [
    "P3 source intake validator checks registered sources, intake decisions, snapshot manifests, source authority records, exclusion logs, and downstream handoff manifests as one artifact set.",
    "Eligible sources must have local hash-bound snapshots; external links without snapshots cannot act as source content.",
    "Visual sources can be frozen for identity but cannot become semantic authority without separate extraction evidence.",
    "Sources that require product capability expansion are routed to human review and cannot become eligible during intake.",
    "Natural-language PRD or brief text remains the primary semantic source; structured inventory records are constrained to index and verification roles.",
    "Rejected sources cannot be named as downstream semantic authority."
  ],
